Chapel approach clearance
-1 1 3 0 10 25 1122 1400 3 18000 0
21003 21004 21005
Midgaard's civic posting boards in the chapel district have been repeatedly damaged by undead remnants pushing up from the Nightfall Catacombs. A chapel carrion bat, a grave skitter acolyte, and a processional ghoul have been identified as the primary threats disrupting the approach routes. Clear these threats from the upper catacomb levels to allow the posting clerk to restore and maintain the chapel-district notice boards.
The chapel district posting boards are intact and secured for the first time in weeks. The undead pressure on the surface approaches has retreated, and the Records Keeper has updated the catacomb hazard map to reflect the cleared zone. Citizens in the chapel district have resumed using the approach routes, and the posting clerk has confirmed the notice circuit is operating on its full schedule again.
